Name: Quality and Safety in Health Informatics
Description: Examination of quality management principles and safety practices in health informatics. Topics include data integrity risk management regulatory compliance and strategies for improving patient outcomes and reducing errors.

Name: Leadership and Ethics in Healthcare
Description: Exploration of leadership theories and ethical principles in healthcare settings. Emphasis on developing leadership skills fostering organizational change and addressing ethical dilemmas in healthcare practice and policy.

Name: Special Topics in Nursing and Health Professions
Description: Study of specialized topics relevant to nursing and health professions. Topics may vary each semester and can include emerging trends current research and interdisciplinary perspectives in healthcare practice and education.

Name: Security and Privacy through Healthcare Technology
Description: Examination of security and privacy issues related to healthcare technology. Topics include data protection confidentiality HIPAA compliance cybersecurity threats and risk mitigation strategies in healthcare settings.

Name: Information Systems and Public Health
Description: Exploration of information systems in public health practice and research. Topics include data collection analysis and dissemination methods for addressing public health challenges and promoting population health outcomes.

Name: Introduction to the Health Care System
Description: Overview of the organization delivery and financing of the healthcare system in the United States. Emphasis on understanding healthcare policy stakeholders and the role of technology in healthcare delivery.

Name: Selected Legal Issues in Criminal Justice
Description: Exploration of selected legal issues within the criminal justice system. Topics may include constitutional rights criminal procedures and legal challenges in contemporary criminal justice practice.

Name: Controversial Legal Issues in Criminal Justice
Description: Analysis of controversial legal issues in criminal justice including debates over policies practices and court decisions. Emphasis on critical examination of diverse perspectives and ethical considerations.

Name: Criminal Evidence
Description: Examination of rules of evidence in criminal proceedings. Topics include admissibility relevance and reliability of evidence as well as the roles of judges and juries in evaluating evidence.

Name: Criminal Justice Policy Analysis
Description: Examination of policy-making processes and their impact on criminal justice practices and outcomes. Emphasis on analyzing policies evaluating alternatives and addressing contemporary issues.

Name: Wrongful Convictions
Description: Investigation of factors contributing to wrongful convictions in the criminal justice system. Emphasis on case studies legal reforms and efforts to prevent and rectify miscarriages of justice.

Name: Prisons and Jails
Description: Examination of the organization management and functions of correctional facilities in the criminal justice system. Topics include inmate rights rehabilitation programs and challenges facing correctional staff.

Name: Community Policing
Description: Exploration of community-oriented approaches to policing. Topics include problem-solving strategies community partnerships and the role of police in promoting public safety and trust.

Name: Family Violence and Criminal Justice
Description: Analysis of family violence within the criminal justice system. Topics include domestic abuse child maltreatment and the legal and social responses to family violence.

Name: Career Planning & Management
Description: Course focusing on career development and planning strategies for students majoring in criminal justice. Emphasis on identifying career goals acquiring relevant skills and navigating job opportunities in the field.

Name: Fundamentals of Painting II
Description: Further exploration of painting techniques and concepts introduced in Fundamentals of Painting I. Emphasis on advanced techniques styles and creative expression.

Name: Fundamentals of Painting I
Description: Introduction to basic painting techniques materials and concepts. Emphasis on developing fundamental skills in painting and creative expression.

Name: Fundamentals of Photography
Description: Introduction to basic principles of photography including camera operation composition and darkroom techniques. Emphasis on developing technical skills and creative vision.
